---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Building | Matt Nash"
  description="Active work across evaluation frameworks, constraint architecture, adversarial eval tooling, and AI welfare research."
>
  <header class="mb-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-serif text-stone-900 mb-2">Building</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm font-mono">Last updated March 2026</p>
  </header>

  <div class="space-y-8">

    <div class="border-l-2 border-stone-200 pl-5">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-stone-900">
          <a href="https://github.com/themattnash/llm-readiness-platform" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="no-underline hover:text-indigo-700 transition-colors">llm-readiness-platform</a>
        </h2>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-emerald-800 bg-emerald-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Complete</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Evaluation framework for LLM-powered features: structured testing, output scoring, and drift
        detection. Eval philosophy, evaluation principles, and metrics taxonomy (7 classes) finalized.
        Working eval harness at v0.2 with ExactMatch, Refusal, and Calibration evaluator classes.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-l-2 border-stone-200 pl-5">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-stone-900">
          <a href="https://github.com/themattnash/constraint-architecture" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="no-underline hover:text-indigo-700 transition-colors">constraint-architecture</a>
        </h2>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-emerald-800 bg-emerald-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Complete</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Reference framework for embedding human judgment, gates, and enforcement layers into AI systems.
        Covers gate taxonomy, guardrail vs. constraint distinction, human judgment layer design, trust
        boundaries, conflict resolution, audit surface, and multi-agent constraint systems.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-l-2 border-stone-200 pl-5">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-stone-900">
          <a href="https://github.com/themattnash/ai-failure-taxonomy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="no-underline hover:text-indigo-700 transition-colors">ai-failure-taxonomy</a>
        </h2>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-amber-800 bg-amber-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">In progress</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Structured taxonomy of AI system failure modes with detection patterns and mitigation playbooks.
        Taxonomy and detection patterns complete across all 9 classes. Mitigation playbooks complete
        for 5 priority classes. Remaining 4 classes in progress.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-l-2 border-stone-200 pl-5">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-stone-900">
          <a href="https://github.com/themattnash/adversarial-eval-tool" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="no-underline hover:text-indigo-700 transition-colors">adversarial-eval-tool</a>
        </h2>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-700 bg-stone-200 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Scoping</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Open-source tool for probing LLM behavioral boundaries and surfacing failure modes. Designed
        to find what standard benchmarks miss. Architecture phase begins April 2026.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
